snippet.textDisplay: I totally understand! I remember when I got my Hulk 181 back in 1997! Wolverine's first appearance! I treated that comic better than my own family! Then in 2003 I went to Comic-Con and had it signed by Len Wein, Herb Trimpe and Stan Lee, then had it appraised by CGC and it came back a 9.8! I thought I was the coolest kid on the planet! Yet, I too still ended up working at a car dealership for 6 years... thank God I'm not doing that anymore! I just graduated bachelors in film and I'm working as an editor! Last I checked, that comic is now worth between 40 and $50,000. I'll never get rid of it!
